    {
      "id": "annot_17",
      "entity_type": "comment_annotation",
      "data": {
        "id": "annot_17",
        "text": "This is a randomized, open-label study. Toxicities and laboratory abnormalities related to abemaciclib treatment (such as diarrhea, neutropenia, and creatinine increase) have the potential to unblind the study, justifying an open-label design. Randomization will occur using an IWRS. Assignment to treatment groups will be determined by a computer-generated random sequence. Each patient in this study will be aware of his or her own assigned treatment group. At each investigative site, all staff involved in treating and caring for study patients will have full knowledge of treatment assignments for the patients under their care.",
